## 🚀 Quick Test: Verify Copilot Setup

```bash
# 1. Create test file
echo "def hello(name: str) -> str:" > test_copilot.py

# 2. Position cursor after ":"
# 3. Press Ctrl+/ (Windows) or Cmd+/ (Mac)
# 4. Wait for suggestion (should complete docstring + return)

# Expected suggestion:
# """Return a greeting message."""
# return f"Hello, {name}!"

# If Copilot doesn't suggest, check:
# - GitHub Copilot extension enabled
# - Signed into GitHub
# - settings.json has correct Python path
# - File has proper syntax
```

